4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 593 of Title 21, unless there is
6 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 A. Any superintendent or school administrator of a school
8 district who knowingly and willfully fails to promptly report or who
9 interferes with the prompt reporting of child abuse and neglect, as
10 mandated in Section 1210.163 of Title 70 of the Oklahoma Statutes
11 shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony punishable by
12 imprisonment in the Department of Corrections for a term of not less
13 than two (2) years, or by a fine of not less than Twenty Thousand
14 Dollars ($20,000.00), or by both such fine and imprisonment. In
15 addition, the court shall require the person to complete a term of
16 community service, without compensation, for a period of hours to be
17 determined by the court.
18 B. As used in this section, "school administrator" means a
19 principal, assistant principal, or any other person who serves in a
20 supervisory or administrative capacity in a school district.
